Four Afghan Police Killed in ‘Mistaken’ NATO Attack on Base

-- B y   E l t a f   N a j a f i z a d a
-- 
2011-08-10T11:53:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-10/four-afghan-police-killed-in-mistaken-nato-attack-on-base.html
Soldiers of NATO’s  International
Security Assistance Force  exchanged fire with Afghan police in
southern Kandahar province, leaving four policemen dead and two
wounded,  Afghanistan ’s Interior Ministry said in an e-mailed
statement.  The troops “mistakenly” shot at a base manned by members
of the Afghan National Police in the province’s Arghandab
district, the statement said.  A spokesman for ISAF, Piaplo Danglo, said by phone that the
force was “aware of the incident and a joint Afghan-ISAF
investigation is currently under way.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eltaf Najafizada in Kabul at 
 enajafizada1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
